Windows
1.	Kill Networking (in powershell) and firewall rules (CLI)
  a.	Disable-netadapter
  b.	$wmi = gwmi –class win32_networkadapter –filter “Name LIKE ‘%<name>%’” [enter] $wmi.disable()
  c.	Netsh advfirewall set currentprofile firewallpolicy blockinboundalways,allowoutbound
  d.	Netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name=”Open <Service>” dir=in action=allow protocol=<tcp | udp> localport=<port number> remoteip=<scoring server ip>
  e.	Netsh advfirewall set currentprofile logging <filepath>
  f.	Netsh advfirewall set allprofile logging droppedconnections enable
  g.	Netsh advfirewall set allprofile logging allowedconnections enable
2.	Rotate Creds and delete unnecessary accounts (CLI)
  a.	Net user
  b.	Net user <username> <new password>
  c.	Net user <username> /delete
  d.	Net localgroup administrators <username> /delete
  e.	Net group “Domain Admins”
  f.	Net share <sharename> /delete
  g.	Create own administrator and delete default admin and guest
  h.	Net group 
3.	What services are running and stop unnecessary (powershell)
  a.	Get-service
  b.	Stop-service <service-name>
  c.	Turn off file sharing and remote desktop
4.	Backup configs (CLI)
  a.	Copy <file path> <new file path>
5.	Check environ for suspicious (both)
  a.	$PATH
  b.	Event viewer
  c.	Task Scheduler
  d.	Get-EventLog
6.	Check Service configs
  a.	Server Manager
    i.	AD
    ii.	DNS
    iii.	DHCP
    iv.	HTTP (IIS)
7.	Restart services and turn interfaces back on (powershell)
  a.	Enable-netadapter
  b.	$wmi = gwmi –class win32_networkadapter –filter “Name LIKE ‘%<name>%’” [enter] $wmi.enable()
  c.	Restart-service <service-name>
8.	Audit Logs
  a.	In Local Security Policy > Local Policies > Audit Policy, audit all for failure
    i.	Block failures
  b.	Disable netbios
  c.	Netdom query WORKSTATION
  d.	Netdom query SERVER
  e.	Host file
    i.	C:\%SystemRoot%\System32\Dns
9.	Check for other bads
  a.	Watch processes
  b.	Disable sticky keys
    i.	Reg add “HKCU\Control Panel\Accessibility\StickyKeys” /v Flags /t REG_SZ /d 506 /f
